>> Assume we use the same network from the previous question for CIFAR-10 images (RGB images with size 32x32) and have the same number of classes at the output (10 classes), how many trainable parameters would our network have? <<

(x) 34 538 {{1st layer: 16 filters of size 5x5x3 + 16 biases = 3*(16*5*5) weights + 16 biases = 1216;
2nd layer: 32 filters of size 5x5x16 + 32 biases = 16*32*5*5 weights + 32biases = 12 832;
FC layer: 8*8*32*10 weights + 10 biases = 20490;
Total: 34 538}}
( ) 34 570 
( ) 86 814 {{RGB does not mean that you have 3x as many parameters as the grayscale model, you need to do the convolution arithmetic per layer.}}
( ) 64 454

||FC layer: 8*8*32*10 weights + 10 biases.||
||Total = 1st layer + 2nd layer + FC layer.||
